<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - DRIVETRAIN FAILURE ANALYSIS - AXLE COMPONENTS - INTER-AXLE
        DIFFERENTIAL
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="2">
        <title>INTER-AXLE DIFFERENTIAL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Spinout.</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">The components in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300251">Figure 51</hotlnk>show the effect of excessive differentiation. The cross
                    is worn and scored, bushings are scored and thrust washers are worn. The side pinion teeth are worn
                    and chipped and the cross shows irregular shaped splines.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300251" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300251" filename="../figg13/G1300251.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 51. Excessive Differentiation</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Case thrust washer surface worn (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1300252">Figure 52</hotlnk>). Metal to metal contact caused this wear pattern in
                    the case wall. The deep ridges at the edge of the pattern requires case replacement.
                </para>
                <figure id="f1300252" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1300252" filename="../figg13/G1300252.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                    <caption>Figure 52. Worn Case Thrust Washer Surface</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
